Interface Alternatives<T extends GoloElement<?>>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CaseStatement, MatchExpression

    public interface Alternatives<T extends GoloElement<?>>
    Alternative nodes, such as `match` or `case`.

    This interface is mainly a fluent builder for a WhenClause container.

    • Method Detail

      • when

        Alternatives<T> when(java.lang.Object cond)
        Defines a new alternative clause.

        This is a builder method.

        Parameters:
        cond - an expression node defining the clause.

      • then

        Alternatives<T> then(java.lang.Object action)
        Defines the action of the previous clause.

        This is a builder method.

        It must be called after a call to when. For instance 

        
  alternative.when(condition).then(action);
        Parameters:
        action - the action to execute in this clause. Its type depends on the kind of alternative (i.e. the WhenClause constructed)
